The number of data customers jumped nearly 10% to 122 million, helping to offset slower adoption for cellular services, particularly in Nigeria. MTN now has 272 million subscribers across 19 markets. Chief Executive Officer Ralph Mupita says the post-Covid-19 recovery was stronger than expected, as the pandemic accelerated digital adoption uptake in areas such as cashless payments and fintech. The group deployed capex of $3 billion to cater for the 53.3% expansion in data traffic and 41.1% increase in fintech volumes over the year. The fintech business now has 57 million monthly active users and generates 10 billion transactions with total transaction value of $16 billion reported in 2021. In constant-currency terms, group service revenue grew by 18.3% to $12 billion. --Monyweb--MTN’s gamble on data and fintech appears to be paying off handsomely, with the number of fintech customers up nearly 20% to 57 million for the year to December 2021.MTN’s gamble on data and fintech appears to be paying off handsomely, with the number of fintech customers up nearly 20% to 57 million for the year to December 2021.